    <h1>Kanha National Park History 2026 — From Royal Hunting to Tiger Reserve</h1>

        <TrustBar category="Travel Guide" readingTime={8} />

        <p class="text-lg italic text-gray-600 mb-6">Last updated: July 18, 2026</p>

    <section class="answer-block">
      <p>
        <strong>Kanha National Park</strong> has a rich history spanning over a century, from royal hunting
        grounds to one of India's most successful tiger reserves. The area was declared a wildlife
        sanctuary in 1933, became a national park on June 1, 1955, and was designated a tiger reserve
        on November 15, 1973 under Project Tiger. The park's conservation journey transformed depleted
        wildlife populations into thriving ecosystems, with tigers recovering from approximately 50-60
        in 1973 to 125+ today, and the hard-ground Barasingha saved from near-extinction (66 animals
        in 1970 to 800+ today). Kanha's history represents one of the world's most successful
        conservation transformations.
      </p>
    </section>

    <Backlink       title="Kanha Accommodation Near Khatia Gate"
      description="Looking for Kanha accommodation near Khatia Gate? Wildmark Resort offers the closest stays to the safari entry with complete packages and expert naturalist guides."
      anchorText="Book Kanha Resort Near Khatia Gate"
      ctaText="Kanha Resort Booking"
      primaryUrl="https://kanhasafaristay.com/blog/wildlife-of-kanha-national-park-beyond-the-tiger/"
      primaryAnchor="Kanha Park History & Wildlife"
      secondaryUrl="https://kanhasafaristay.com/"
      secondaryAnchor="Book Kanha Heritage Safari"
      tertiaryUrl="https://kanhasafaristay.com/faq/"
      tertiaryAnchor="Kanha History FAQ"
